  VERSION="2.1.1"
 CATEGORY="audio-player"
ATTRIBUTE="x11"
 HOMEPAGE="http://www.freeamp.org"
      URL="download/src"
      REQ="musicbrainz gdk-pixbuf"
   OPT[0]="libvorbis:::to play oggvorbis files"
   OPT[1]="freetype1:::to enable use of truetype fonts"
   OPT[2]="ORBit:::to enable a remote Cobra interface"
   OPT[3]="nasm:::to enable assembly optimizations"
   OPT[4]="esound::--disable-esd:to enable esd output"
FRESHMEAT="freeamp"
    SHORT="FreeAmp is an extensible, cross-platform audio player."
cat << EOF
FreeAmp is an extensible, cross-platform audio player. 
It features an optimized version of the GPLed Xing MPEG decoder 
which makes it one of the fastest and best sounding players available. 
FreeAmp provides a number of the most common features users have come 
to expect in a clean, easy to use interface.
EOF
